{
  "texts": [
    "40 Our estimated productivity gains are closer to those of Acemoglu (2025), though for different reasons.",
    "While Acemoglu (2025) combines the experimental productivity estimates with a calibrated adoption curve, we measure both adoption and (self-reported) time savings directly.",
    "Bick, Blandin and Deming (2025) provide a thoughtful comparison between their survey-based estimates of productivity gains and the predictions of Acemoglu (2025).",
    "41 Our time savings estimates align more closely with those of Bick, Blandin and Deming (2025), who, in a nationally representative U.S. survey, find an average reported time savings of 5.4% among users.",
    "However, their study does not split the time savings by occupation or employer policies, limiting direct comparability to our estimates."
  ]
}